name: KLM A330-203 [PH-AOD] Overhead Landing at Edmonton Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
At the end of May, KLM, the flag carrier of the Netherlands, started flights to Edmonton International Airport from Amsterdam, operating four times a week. I had some stuff to do in Edmonton and thankfully it worked out so that I could catch this bird on the way home. Here we have PH-AOD passing overhead and landing on runway 30, with some taxi footage included. Don't expect too many uploads from YEG, the six hours of driving there and back really is tough to justify when there's not a lot of traffic. If there's an Antonov or something rare, on the other hand...

Thanks for watching! Please comment, rate, and subscribe!
